        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 11 at 5:25PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 525 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 4 miles
southwest of Adair, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Pensacola...                      Big Cabin...
Adair...                          Pryor...
Chelsea...                        Pryor Creek...
White Oak...                      Bushyhead...
Foyil...                          Sportsmen Acres Community...

This includes Interstate 44 between mile markers 255 and 281.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
